26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_fuse_base.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:34 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "priv.h"
30
31u32
32nvkm_fuse_read(struct nvkm_fuse *fuse, u32 addr)
33{
34 return fuse->func->read(fuse, addr);
35}
36
37static void *
38nvkm_fuse_dtor(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
39{
40 return nvkm_fuse(subdev);
41}
42
43static const struct nvkm_subdev_func
44nvkm_fuse = {
45 .dtor = nvkm_fuse_dtor,
46};
47
48int
49nvkm_fuse_new_(const struct nvkm_fuse_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
50 int index, struct nvkm_fuse **pfuse)
51{
52 struct nvkm_fuse *fuse;
53 if (!(fuse = *pfuse = kzalloc(sizeof(*fuse), GFP_KERNEL)))
54 return -ENOMEM;
55 nvkm_subdev_ctor(&nvkm_fuse, device, index, 0, &fuse->subdev);
56 fuse->func = func;
57 spin_lock_init(&fuse->lock);
58 return 0;
59}
